# TradeYantra master Caddyfile.
#
# The provisioner writes one snippet per tenant into ./tenants/<id>.caddy and
# reloads Caddy. Each snippet routes a subdomain to that tenant's container ports
# and Caddy auto-issues TLS per subdomain (HTTP-01) as long as the subdomain's
# DNS points at this host.
#
# Run Caddy with this file, e.g.:
#   caddy run --config saas/provisioner/caddy/Caddyfile
# or reload after a change:
#   caddy reload --config saas/provisioner/caddy/Caddyfile

{
	# ACME contact for Let's Encrypt certificates.
	email admin@tradeyantra.in
}

# Per-tenant site blocks (generated). A glob that matches nothing is fine.
import tenants/*.caddy
